    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Sylvia Ann Hewlett (''Have a Child, and Experience the Wage Gap,'' Op-Ed, May 16) is wrong when she argues that parents should get additional assistance, like paid leave, to ease the costs of raising a family. The government already rewards parents with tax credits.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Sylvia Ann Hewlett (''Have a Child, and Experience the Wage Gap,'' Op-Ed, May 16) is wrong when she argues that parents should get additional assistance, like paid leave, to ease the costs of raising a family. The government already rewards parents with tax credits.</p>
        <p>Ms. Hewlett should remember that having children is a choice; adults who choose to have children should bear the costs of their choice.</p>
        <p>JAMES WHITING  Brooklyn, May 17, 2000</p>
      </block>
